Abstracts:

Abstracts, which will appear in the official conference program, should adhere
to the following guidelines:

The abstract shall:

-	accurately describe the proposed presentation;
-	should not exceed  250 words, and must be written in French;
-	be composed using word processing software;
-	use size 12 Times New Roman font and be single spaced; 
-	be formatted to fit a US letter page (21,59 cm x 27,94 cm) with top and bottom
margins set at 9 cm, and left and right margins set at 3,3 cm.

Please neatly draw in black ink any symbols that cannot be replicated by a word
processor.

Please note that the review committee does not ensure a systematic linguistic
review of each document, but will exercise its right to correct formatting
errors as well as make suggestions regarding content.

Important instructions:

-	Please send abstracts (in MS Word format ) as email attachments to
jdl@lli.ulaval.ca by 19 January 2007. 
-	Abstracts should be saved with the following title: jdl followed by your
initials (i.e.  jdlabc.doc).
-	Please provide the review committee with any special font (aside from the API
characters provided by the SIL at www.sil.org) used in the abstract.

Documents to include:

To expedite the registration process, please include the following documents in
your  proposition package:

1.	The Proposition de communication form, properly completed. This form will be
available shortly on the following website: http://www.lli.ulaval.ca/JDL.html.
2.	A check for $15 CDN payable to the Journées de linguistique. International
students will assume any transaction costs that may be charged by their
respective financial institutions.

